ou improve your typing <strong>speed</strong>, this lesson will get you around the track in no time.</p><h4>Rules of the Game</h4><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson allows you a <span class=\"strong\">12% error margin</span>.  That\\\\\'s a lot, so this allows you to type quickly, and not worry about accuracy as much.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As always, we will be timing you.  From the time you type the first character until you hit the last letter, the timer will be going.  Try to use this to your advantage.  Watch your speed and try to beat that speed on the next exercise.  It\\\\\'s all about timing here!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">If you make too many mistakes, try again slower.  If you made no mistakes or only a few, try the next exercise faster.</p>','Keyboard',8,0,1,1),(72,9,'Дунд шатыг дуусгах','Intermediate Wrap Up','<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are making amazing progress!  This is your final test before moving on to the Advanced Course.  This lesson is going to challenge everything you\\\'ve learned so far, starting with random letters and punctuation, and moving into difficult sentences featuring both punctuation AND numbers!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Remember to keep your eyes off your hands! This lesson is quite the exercise!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are making amazing progress!  This is your final test before moving on to the Advanced Course.  This lesson is going to challenge everything you\\\\\'ve learned so far, starting with random letters and punctuation, and moving into difficult sentences featuring both punctuation AND numbers!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Remember to keep your eyes off your hands! This lesson is quite the exercise!</p>','Keyboard',9,0,1,0),(73,10,'Гарыг хэсэгчилэх','Keyboard Quadrants','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Welcome to the advanced Quadrants lesson.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This 16 exercise lesson is broken into 4 sections, each concentrating on a particular quarter of the keyboard.  We will begin with the top left keys.  Stretch out your left hand, and crack those knuckles if you need to!  Your right hand can relax sometimes, but will still be required.</p><p class=\"typing help\">And, being that this is an advanced lesson, you have to maintain at least 94% accuracy... so take your time and concentrate on hitting the right keys.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Enjoy!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Welcome to the advanced Quadrants lesson.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This 16 exercise lesson is broken into 4 sections, each concentrating on a particular quarter of the keyboard.  We will begin with the top left keys.  Stretch out your left hand, and crack those knuckles if you need to!  Your right hand can relax sometimes, but will still be required.</p><p class=\"typing help\">And, being that this is an advanced lesson, you have to maintain at least 94% accuracy... so take your time and concentrate on hitting the right keys.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Enjoy!</p>','Keyboard',1,0,1,0),(74,10,'Ур чадвар Зохиогч Дасгалууд','Skill Builder Drills','<p class=\"typinghelp\">These advanced exercises feature often large, complex words, meant to tangle the fingers. Stretch your hands out and get yourself into the zone.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Your accuracy must be 93% or better, so take it slow and concentrate on hitting the right keys.  Don\\\'t worry, the speed will come.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">These advanced exercises feature often large, complex words, meant to tangle the fingers. Stretch your hands out and get yourself into the zone.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Your accuracy must be 93% or better, so take it slow and concentrate on hitting the right keys.  Don\\\\\'t worry, the speed will come.</p>','Keyboard',2,0,1,0),(75,10,'Тэмдэг, Нарийвчилсан Цэг таслал','Symbols and Advanced Punctuation','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve mastered the standard keyboard, lets move into advanced punctuation!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson features punctuation that requires you to the shift key both on the standard rows as well as on the numbers above.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve mastered the standard keyboard, lets move into advanced punctuation!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson features punctuation that requires you to the shift key both on the standard rows as well as on the numbers above.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>','Keyboard',3,0,1,0),(76,10,'Нямбай дасгалууд','Accuracy Drills','<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing simple paragraphs containing all the letters of the alphabet,numbers, and special symbols.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboardbefore starting the exercise.  Remember, hold the shift (or alternate key on non-US keyboards) to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Eventually we will be concentrating on certain letters but you must know simple touch typing first.When you finish all of this, you will be a typing master.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing simple paragraphs containing all the letters of the alphabet,numbers, and special symbols.  If you don\\\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboardbefore starting the exercise.  Remember, hold the shift (or alternate key on non-US keyboards) to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Eventually we will be concentrating on certain letters but you must know simple touch typing first.When you finish all of this, you will be a typing master.</p>','Keyboard',4,0,1,0),(77,10,'Цифр Товчлуур','The Numeric Keypad','<p class=\"typinghelp\">This lessons is provided for practice with the numeric keypad available on just about every keyboard (and some laptops).  You do not need to know touch typing on the standard keyboard in order to learn touch typing on the 10-key number pad.  So, you can begin this series right away.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">When entering numeric values, accuracy is always more important than speed. Take these lessons very slowly.  Speed will come naturally later.  The <strong>accuracy level is set to 2%</strong>, so that does not leave you a very large error margin.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As with the standard keypad, you must start in the HOME position.  Place the first three fingers of your right hand over the <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>4</key></span> <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>5</key></span> and <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>6</key></span> keys of the keypad.  Your fingers should be poised just over the keys gently brushing them.  Use your pinkie to press ENTER and use the thumb of your left hand for spaces when necessary.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\"><span class=\"strong\">NOTE:  Make sure the <em>NUM LOCK</em> is on (a little light should shine on the keyboard.)</span></p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">This lessons is provided for practice with the numeric keypad available on just about every keyboard (and some laptops).  You do not need to know touch typing on the standard keyboard in order to learn touch typing on the 10-key number pad.  So, you can begin this series right away.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">When entering numeric values, accuracy is always more important than speed. Take these lessons very slowly.  Speed will come naturally later.  The <strong>accuracy level is set to 2%</strong>, so that does not leave you a very large error margin.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As with the standard keypad, you must start in the HOME position.  Place the first three fingers of your right hand over the <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>4</key></span> <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>5</key></span> and <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>6</key></span> keys of the keypad.  Your fingers should be poised just over the keys gently brushing them.  Use your pinkie to press ENTER and use the thumb of your left hand for spaces when necessary.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\"><span class=\"strong\">NOTE:  Make sure the <em>NUM LOCK</em> is on (a little light should shine on the keyboard.)</span></p>','Keypad',5,0,1,1),(78,10,'Гүнзгий шатыг дуусгах','Advanced Wrap Up','<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing mostly full paragraphs containing all kinds of letters, numbers, punctuation, etc.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboard before starting the exercise.  Remember, hold down shift to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Just take your time and focus on accuracy.  You\\\'re already in the Advanced Course, so this should be a breeze for you.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing mostly full paragraphs containing all kinds of letters, numbers, punctuation, etc.  If you don\\\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboard before starting the exercise.  Remember, hold down shift to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Just take your time and focus on accuracy.  You\\\\\'re already in the Advanced Course, so this should be a breeze for you.</p>','Keyboard',6,0,1,0),(113,12,'Common Medical Terms ','Common Medical Terms','<img src=\"/uploads/medical_terms.png\" align=\"right\" /><p class=\"typinghelp\" /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />This lesson features very long and difficult to type medical terms to help strengthen your ability to remember the keyboard and not just typing common words.  This lesson is also great for medical transcriptionists as you will be seeing these terms very often!<br /></p>','<img src=\"/uploads/medical_terms.png\" align=\"right\" /><p class=\"typinghelp\" /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />This lesson features very long and difficult to type medical terms to help strengthen your ability to remember the keyboard and not just typing common words.  This lesson is also great for medical transcriptionists as you will be seeing these terms very often!<br /></p>','Keyboard',1,1,1,0),(114,1