les - In a Thousand Years','<img src=\"/uploads/aesop.png\" align=\"right\" /><br /><br /><br /><p class=\"typinghelp\"><div align=\"center\"><br /><strong>In a Thousand Years (Aesop Fables) <br /><br />by Hans Christian Andersen<br /><br />(1805-1875)</strong></div></p>','<img src=\"/uploads/aesop.png\" align=\"right\" /><br /><br /><br /><p class=\"typinghelp\"><div align=\"center\"><br /><strong>In a Thousand Years (Aesop Fables) <br /><br />by Hans Christian Andersen<br /><br />(1805-1875)</strong></div></p>','Keyboard',11,1,1,0),(124,12,'Aesop Fables - Short Stories','Aesop Fables - Short Stories','<img src=\"/uploads/aesop.png\" align=\"right\" /><br /><br /><br /><p class=\"typinghelp\"><div align=\"center\"><br /><strong>Short Stories from the Aesop Fables<br /><br />by Various Authors<br /><br />(900-1879)</strong></div></p>','<img src=\"/uploads/aesop.png\" align=\"right\" /><br /><br /><br /><p class=\"typinghelp\"><div align=\"center\"><br /><strong>Short Stories from the Aesop Fables<br /><br />by Various Authors<br /><br />(900-1879)</strong></div></p>','',12,1,1,0),(125,8,'Index Finger Workout','Index Finger Workout','<img src=\"/uploads/finger_workout.png\" align=\"right\" /><p class=\"typinghelp\" /><br /><br /><br /><br />Таны хуруунууд дасгалтай уулзах цаг боллоо! Бид таны долоовор хурууг ажиллуулж эхлүүлэх гэж байна (эрхий хурууны дараах эхний хуруу). Хурууныхаа булчинг зохих ёсоор ажиллуулахын тулд энэ хичээлийг олон удаа хийхийг танд зөвлөж байна.<br /></p>','<img src=\"/uploads/finger_workout.png\" align=\"right\" /><p class=\"typinghelp\" /><br /><br /><br /><br />It\\\'s time for your fingers to hit the gym!  We\\\'re going to start you out by working out your index finger (the first finger after your thumb).  I recommend you do this lesson multiple times to really work your finger\\\'s muscles.<br /></p>','keyboard',13,1,1,0),(126,9,'Ring Finger Workout','Ring Finger Workout','<img src=\"/uploads/finger_workout.png\" align=\"right\" /><p class=\"typinghelp\" /><br /><br /><br /><br />Wow, your fingers are looking pretty ripped.  Again, we will be working the familiar workout routine, but this time with the ring finger, found 3 fingers over from the thumb.  Good luck!<br /></p>','<img src=\"/uploads/finger_workout.png\" align=\"right\" /><p class=\"typinghelp\" /><br /><br /><br /><br />Wow, your fingers are looking pretty ripped.  Again, we will be working the familiar workout routine, but this time with the ring finger, found 3 fingers over from the thumb.  Good luck!<br /></p>','keyboard',14,1,1,0),(127,8,'Middle Finger Workout','Middle Finger Workout','<img src=\"/uploads/finger_workout.png\" align=\"right\" /><p class=\"typinghelp\" /><br /><br /><br /><br />За, Одоо таны долоовор хуруу тод цохиж байгаа тул бид дунд хуруу руу шилжин орж байна (эрхий хуруунаас хоёр дахь хуруу). Энэ хичээл нь хурууныхаа булчинг бэхжүүлэх, хуруугаа байрлуулахад дасгал хийхэд туслах ерөнхий дасгалуудыг багтаасан болно.<br /></p>','<img src=\"/uploads/finger_workout.png\" align=\"right\" /><p class=\"typinghelp\" /><br /><br /><br /><br />Alrighty, now that your index finger is nice and buff, we\\\\\'re going to move into the middle finger (the second finger over from your thumb).  This lesson features the same general drills to help strengthen your finger\\\\\'s muscles as well as drill you on finger placement.<br /></p>','keyboard',15,1,1,0),(128,9,'Pinky Finger Workout','Pinky Finger Workout','<img src=\"/uploads/finger_workout.png\" align=\"right\" /><p class=\"typinghelp\" /><br /><br /><br /><br />Wow you\\\'re doing great!  You\\\'ve managed to move all the way down the line to the pinky finger!  This is the last finger on your hand and will be the most difficult to get used to using properly.  I recommend you type this lesson many times!<br /></p>','<img src=\"/uploads/finger_workout.png\" align=\"right\" /><p class=\"typinghelp\" /><br /><br /><br /><br />Wow you\\\\\'re doing great!  You\\\\\'ve managed to move all the way down the line to the pinky finger!  This is the last finger on your hand and will be the most difficult to get used to using properly.  I recommend you type this lesson many times!<br /></p>','keyboard',16,1,1,0),(316,1,'Нүүр Мөрны Товчнууд','The Home Row Keys','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Бид \"Үндсэн Мөр\" дээр эхэлж <strong>долоовор хуруугаараа <key>F</key> ба <key>J</key> товчнуудыг сурч эхэлнэ</strong>.<p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Зөвлөмж: Таны гар дээрх эдгээр товчлуурууд нь <strong>өргөгдсөн товгор</strong> байгааг анзаараарай. Эдгээр товгор-ууд нь таны гар руу доош харуулахгүйгээр, үндсэн мөрийг <strong>гараараа мэдэрч хайх боломжийг олгоно</strong>.</p><br /><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/f_j.png\" alt=\"Home row Finger Position\" /></center>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">We are going to begin on the \"Home Row\", <strong>learning the <key>F</key> and <key>J</key> keys</strong> with your index fingers. <p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Tip: Notice the <strong>raised bumps</strong> on these keys on your keyboard. These bumps allow you to <strong>find the home row by touch</strong>, without looking down at your keyboard.</p><br /><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/f_j.png\" alt=\"Home row Finger Position\" /></center>','Keyboard',1,0,1,1),(317,1,'Дээд Мөрны Товчнууд','The Top Row Keys','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Бид одоо Дээд Мөр гэж нэрлэдэг, Үндсэн Мөрийн яг дээрх товчнууд шилжиж байна. Бид <strong><key>R</key> болон <key>U</key> товч</strong>лууруудаас эхэлж долоовор хуруугаараа бичиж эхэлнэ.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\"><strong>Үндсэн мөр дээр хуруугаа байлгаж байхаа санаж байгаарай</strong>, зөвхөн нэг хуруугаа нэг л хөдөлгөнө.</p><br /><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/r_u.png\" alt=\"Дээд эгнээний хурууны байршил\" /></center>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">We are now going to move into the keys just above the Home Row, known as the Top Row.  We will begin with <strong>the <key>R</key> and <key>U</key> keys</strong> which you will type with your index fingers.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Remember to always <strong>keep your fingers resting on the Home Row</strong>, and only move one finger at a time.</p><br /><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/r_u.png\" alt=\"Home row Finger Position\" /></center>','Keyboard',2,0,1,1),(318,1,'Доод Мөрны Товчнууд','The Bottom Keys','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Одоо та Үндсэн Мөр ба Дээд Мөрийн товчнуудыг тухай мэдэж авсан тул бид Доод Мөр рүү шилжих болно. Бид долоотор хуруугаар <strong><key>V</key> ба <key>M</key> товч</strong>луур дарж эхэлнэ. </p><br /><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/v_m.png\" alt=\"Доод эгнээний хурууны байршил\" /></center>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you are feeling comfortable with the Home Row and Top Row keys, we will move to the Bottom Row.  We will start out with the index fingers reaching down to <strong>the <key>V</key> and <key>M</key> keys</strong>.</p><br /><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/v_m.png\" alt=\"Bottom Row Finger Position\" /></center>','Keyboard',3,0,1,1),(319,1,'Амархан Нүүр Мөрны үгс','Easy Home Row Words','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Одоо та хуруугаа зөв байрлуулж, аль хуруугаа аль товчлуурыг цохиж, Бид Үндсэн Мөр дээрхээс эхэлдэг үгсийг бичихэд хялбар болж өөрчлөгдсөн тул амжилтанд хүрэх болно.</p><p><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/all_keys.png\" alt=\"Гарны Хурууны Байрлал\" /></center><br /></p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Үсэг бичсэнийхээ дараа үндсэн мөрд таны хуруу буцахыг үргэлж санаж байх. Хэрвээ та аль хуруугаараа товч дарах ёстой гэдэгт эргэлзэж байвал дэлгэц дээрх гар ба гаруудаа лавлаж хараарай. Аль болох та гараасаа нүдээ салгахыг оролдоорой. Амжилт хүсье!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve got a hold on proper finger placement and which fingers hit which keys, we\\\'re going to kick it up a notch by moving into short, easy to type words that all start on the Home Row.</p><p><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/all_keys.png\" alt=\"Keyboard Finger Position\" /></center><br /></p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Always remember to return your finger to the home row after typing a letter.  Refer to the onscreen keyboard and hands if you are unsure as to which finger should press the key.  Try to keep your eyes off your hands as much as possible.  Good luck!</p>','Keyboard',6,0,1,1),(320,1,'Амархан Дээд Мөрны үгс','Easy Top Row Words','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Rinse and repeat!  We\\\'re now going to move on to words whose first letter originates on the top row.  The words are mostly simple.. mostly!  You may occasionally run across a word that will trip you up, just to keep you on your toes!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Та үг бүр бичихийн өмнө таны хуруунууд үндсэн мөр дээр байгааг шалгаарай. Хэрвээ та аль хуруугаараа товч дарах ёстой гэдэгт эргэлзэж байвал дэлгэц дээрх гар ба гаруудаа лавлаж хараарай. Аль болох та гараасаа нүдээ салгахыг оролдоорой. Амжилт хүсье!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Rinse and repeat!  We\\\\\'re now going to move on to words whose first letter originates on the top row.  The words are mostly simple.. mostly!  You may occasionally run across a word that will trip you up, just to keep you on your toes!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Make sure your fingers are on the home row before you type each word.  Refer to the onscreen keyboard and hands if you are unsure as to which finger should press the key.  Try to keep your eyes off your hands as much as possible.  Good luck!</p>','Keyboard',7,0,1,1),(321,1,'Амархан Доод Мөрны үгс','Easy Bottom Row Words','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Доод мөр! Бид одоо энхний үсэг нь доод мөр дээр байралдаг үгнүүд рүү шилжин орж байна. Эдгээр үгсүүд магадгүй жаахан ... хөгжилтэй!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Та үг бүр бичихийн өмнө таны хуруунууд үндсэн мөр дээр байгааг шалгаарай. Хэрвээ та аль хуруугаараа товч дарах ёстой гэдэгт эргэлзэж байвал дэлгэц дээрх гар ба гаруудаа лавлаж хараарай. Аль болох та гараасаа нүдээ салгахыг оролдоорой. Амжилт хүсье!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">And last but not least, the bottom row!  We\\\\\'re now going to move onto words whose first letter originates on the bottom row, then branches out.  These words may be a little... funky!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Make sure your fingers are on the home row before you type each word.  Refer to the onscreen keyboard and hands if you are unsure as to which finger should press the key.  Try to keep your eyes off your hands as much as possible.  Good luck!</p>','Keyboard',8,0,1,1),(322,2,'Том үсгээр хямралын сурах','Learn to Bust a Capital Letter','<p class=\"typinghelp\">It\\\'s time to <strong>shift</strong> things into gear.  This lesson is going to teach you to capitalize letters on your keyboard.  To make a letter uppercase, hold down the SHIFT key while pressing the letter key.  It\\\'s that simple!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">The tip of the day is to shift with the hand opposite of the hand that is typing the uppercase letter.  So if you type an uppercase <key>F</key>, you should use your right hand shift.</p><br /><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/shift_keys.png\" alt=\"Home row Finger Position\" /></center>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">It\\\\\'s time to <strong>shift</strong> things into gear.  This lesson is going to teach you to capitalize letters on your keyboard.  To make a letter uppercase, hold down the SHIFT key while pressing the letter key.  It\\\\\'s that simple!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">The tip of the day is to shift with the hand opposite of the hand that is typing the uppercase letter.  So if you type an uppercase <key>F</key>, you should use your right hand shift.</p><br /><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/shift_keys.png\" alt=\"Home row Finger Position\" /></center>','Keyboard',3,0,1,1),(323,2,'Том үгийн хямралыг сурах','Learn to Bust a Capital Word','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve got a feel for shifting individual letters, lets move into typing words that start with a capital letter.  You may find this lesson challenging, but always remember proper form, keeping your hands on the home row, and to shift with the opposite hand.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">While typing this lesson, do your best to keep your eyes on the screen and off of your hands.  If you can\\\'t remember where a key is, use the onscreen keyboard and hands to help you type it.  Your key to typing fast is remembering where the keys are without looking!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve got a feel for shifting individual letters, lets move into typing words that start with a capital letter.  You may find this lesson challenging, but always remember proper form, keeping your hands on the home row, and to shift with the opposite hand.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">While typing this lesson, do your best to keep your eyes on the screen and off of your hands.  If you can\\\'t remember where a key is, use the onscreen keyboard and hands to help you type it.  Your key to typing fast is remembering where the keys are without looking!</p>','Keyboard',4,0,1,1),(324,1,'Эхлэгч шатыг дуусгах','Beginner Wrap Up','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Тиймээ та энэ хүртэл хийж чадлаа. сайн ажиллаа! Энэ бол Дурд Курс руу шилжихийн өмнөх таны сүүлийн тест юм. Энэ хичээл нь таны энэ хүртэлэх сурсан, Үндсэн Мөрөөс эхлээд бүх зүйлээр сорих бөгөөд бүтэн өгүүлбэр рүү орно.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Гарнаасаа нүдээ салгахаа санаарай! Та мөгөдгүй спортын ундаа барж авахыг хүсэх байх учир нь энэ хичээл таныг хөлөрүүлэх болно.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">So you\\\\\'ve made it this far eh?  Great job!  This is your final test before moving on to the Intermediate Course.  This lesson is going to challenge everything you\\\\\'ve learned so far, starting with the home row, and moving into full sentences!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Remember to keep your eyes off your hands! You may want to grab a sports drink because this lesson will make you sweat!</p>','Keyboard',9,0,1,1),(325,2,'Цагаан толгойн (A-M) сэргээх','Alphabet Soup (A-M)','<p class=\"typinghelp\">This two part lesson contains one exercise for each letter of the alphabet.  In this lesson we will start at \"A\" and end at \"M\", but will not work on numbers or punctuation.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Each exercise will focus on hitting keys on every row of the keyboard after the first letter key is hit.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">This two part lesson contains one exercise for each letter of the alphabet.  In this lesson we will start at \"A\" and end at \"M\", but will not work on numbers or punctuation.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Each exercise will focus on hitting keys on every row of the keyboard after the first letter key is hit.</p>','Keyboard',1,0,1,1),(326,2,'Цагаан толгойн (N-Z) сэргээх','Alphabet Soup (N-Z)','<p class=\"typinghelp\">This two part lesson contains one exercise for each letter of the alphabet.  In this lesson we will start at \"N\" and end at \"Z\", but will not work on numbers or punctuation.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Each exercise will focus on hitting keys on every row of the keyboard after the first letter key is hit.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">This two part lesson contains one exercise for each letter of the alphabet.  In this lesson we will start at \"N\" and end at \"Z\", but will not work on numbers or punctuation.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Each exercise will focus on hitting keys on every row of the keyboard after the first letter key is hit.</p>','Keyboard',2,0,1,1),(327,2,'Үндсэн Цэг Тэмдэглэл','Basic Punctuation','<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are now ready to move into basic punctuation.  This lesson will introduce you to punctuation that, depending on your keyboard format, does not require you to hit the shift key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">You will be doing a lot of typing with your right hand, so make sure to stretch it out first!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are now ready to move into basic punctuation.  This lesson will introduce you to punctuation that, depending on your keyboard format, does not require you to hit the shift key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">You will be doing a lot of typing with your right hand, so make sure to stretch it out first!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>','Keyboard',5,0,1,1),(328,2,'Хамгийн нийтлэг үгс Англи хэл','Most Common English Words','<p class=\"typinghelp\">This one should be fun.  This exercise is a run down of the 300 most used English words. These are words that you will be typing very often during your typing career.  It is recommended you practice this lesson many times!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Don\\\'t forget to keep your eyes off your keyboard!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">This one should be fun.  This exercise is a run down of the 300 most used English words. These are words that you will be typing very often during your typing career.  It is recommended you practice this lesson many times!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Don\\\\\'t forget to keep your eyes off your keyboard!</p>','Keyboard',6,0,1,1),(329,2,'Хурд Үзүүлэх Сургалт','Speed Drills','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Designed to help you improve your typing <strong>speed</strong>, this lesson will get you around the track in no time.</p><h4>Rules of the Game</h4><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson allows you a <span class=\"strong\">12% error margin</span>.  That\\\'s a lot, so this allows you to type quickly, and not worry about accuracy as much.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As always, we will be timing you.  From the time you type the first character until you hit the last letter, the timer will be going.  Try to use this to your advantage.  Watch your speed and try to beat that speed on the next exercise.  It\\\'s all about timing here!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">If you make too many mistakes, try again slower.  If you made no mistakes or only a few, try the next exercise faster.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Designed to help you improve your typing <strong>speed</strong>, this lesson will get you around the track in no time.</p><h4>Rules of the Game</h4><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson allows you a <span class=\"strong\">12% error margin</span>.  That\\\\\'s a lot, so this allows you to type quickly, and not worry about accuracy as much.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As always, we will be timing you.  From the time you type the first character until you hit the last letter, the timer will be going.  Try to use this to your advantage.  Watch your speed and try to beat that speed on the next exercise.  It\\\\\'s all about timing here!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">If you make too many mistakes, try again slower.  If you made no mistakes or only a few, try the next exercise faster.</p>','Keyboard',8,0,1,1),(330,2,'Тооллого Захидал Тоо','Numbers Letters Numbers','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Moving on up above the home row, you are going to learn how to hit the number keys.  Always remember to return your finger to its proper home row position after typing a letter or number. The numbers are broken up by finger allowing you to always practice proper finger movement.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">If you forget which finger should hit which key, refer to the onscreen keyboard and hand diagrams.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Moving on up above the home row, you are going to learn how to hit the number keys.  Always remember to return your finger to its proper home row position after typing a letter or number. The numbers are broken up by finger allowing you to always practice proper finger movement.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">If you forget which finger should hit which key, refer to the onscreen keyboard and hand diagrams.</p>','Keyboard',7,0,1,1),(331,2,'Дунд шатыг дуусгах','Intermediate Wrap Up','<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are making amazing progress!  This is your final test before moving on to the Advanced Course.  This lesson is going to challenge everything you\\\'ve learned so far, starting with random letters and punctuation, and moving into difficult sentences featuring both punctuation AND numbers!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Remember to keep your eyes off your hands! This lesson is quite the exercise!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">You are making amazing progress!  This is your final test before moving on to the Advanced Course.  This lesson is going to challenge everything you\\\\\'ve learned so far, starting with random letters and punctuation, and moving into difficult sentences featuring both punctuation AND numbers!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Remember to keep your eyes off your hands! This lesson is quite the exercise!</p>','Keyboard',9,0,1,1),(332,3,'Гарыг хэсэгчилэх','Keyboard Quadrants','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Welcome to the advanced Quadrants lesson.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This 16 exercise lesson is broken into 4 sections, each concentrating on a particular quarter of the keyboard.  We will begin with the top left keys.  Stretch out your left hand, and crack those knuckles if you need to!  Your right hand can relax sometimes, but will still be required.</p><p class=\"typing help\">And, being that this is an advanced lesson, you have to maintain at least 94% accuracy... so take your time and concentrate on hitting the right keys.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Enjoy!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Welcome to the advanced Quadrants lesson.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This 16 exercise lesson is broken into 4 sections, each concentrating on a particular quarter of the keyboard.  We will begin with the top left keys.  Stretch out your left hand, and crack those knuckles if you need to!  Your right hand can relax sometimes, but will still be required.</p><p class=\"typing help\">And, being that this is an advanced lesson, you have to maintain at least 94% accuracy... so take your time and concentrate on hitting the right keys.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Enjoy!</p>','Keyboard',1,0,1,0),(333,3,'Ур чадвар Зохиогч Дасгалууд','Skill Builder Drills','<p class=\"typinghelp\">These advanced exercises feature often large, complex words, meant to tangle the fingers. Stretch your hands out and get yourself into the zone.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Your accuracy must be 93% or better, so take it slow and concentrate on hitting the right keys.  Don\\\'t worry, the speed will come.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">These advanced exercises feature often large, complex words, meant to tangle the fingers. Stretch your hands out and get yourself into the zone.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Your accuracy must be 93% or better, so take it slow and concentrate on hitting the right keys.  Don\\\\\'t worry, the speed will come.</p>','Keyboard',2,0,1,0),(334,3,'Тэмдэг, Нарийвчилсан Цэг таслал','Symbols and Advanced Punctuation','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve mastered the standard keyboard, lets move into advanced punctuation!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson features punctuation that requires you to the shift key both on the standard rows as well as on the numbers above.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Now that you\\\'ve mastered the standard keyboard, lets move into advanced punctuation!</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">This lesson features punctuation that requires you to the shift key both on the standard rows as well as on the numbers above.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Good luck, and have fun!</p>','Keyboard',3,0,1,0),(335,3,'Нямбай дасгалууд','Accuracy Drills','<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing simple paragraphs containing all the letters of the alphabet,numbers, and special symbols.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboardbefore starting the exercise.  Remember, hold the shift (or alternate key on non-US keyboards) to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Eventually we will be concentrating on certain letters but you must know simple touch typing first.When you finish all of this, you will be a typing master.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing simple paragraphs containing all the letters of the alphabet,numbers, and special symbols.  If you don\\\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboardbefore starting the exercise.  Remember, hold the shift (or alternate key on non-US keyboards) to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Eventually we will be concentrating on certain letters but you must know simple touch typing first.When you finish all of this, you will be a typing master.</p>','Keyboard',4,0,1,0),(336,3,'Цифр Товчлуур','The Numeric Keypad','<p class=\"typinghelp\">This lessons is provided for practice with the numeric keypad available on just about every keyboard (and some laptops).  You do not need to know touch typing on the standard keyboard in order to learn touch typing on the 10-key number pad.  So, you can begin this series right away.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">When entering numeric values, accuracy is always more important than speed. Take these lessons very slowly.  Speed will come naturally later.  The <strong>accuracy level is set to 2%</strong>, so that does not leave you a very large error margin.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As with the standard keypad, you must start in the HOME position.  Place the first three fingers of your right hand over the <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>4</key></span> <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>5</key></span> and <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>6</key></span> keys of the keypad.  Your fingers should be poised just over the keys gently brushing them.  Use your pinkie to press ENTER and use the thumb of your left hand for spaces when necessary.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\"><span class=\"strong\">NOTE:  Make sure the <em>NUM LOCK</em> is on (a little light should shine on the keyboard.)</span></p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">This lessons is provided for practice with the numeric keypad available on just about every keyboard (and some laptops).  You do not need to know touch typing on the standard keyboard in order to learn touch typing on the 10-key number pad.  So, you can begin this series right away.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">When entering numeric values, accuracy is always more important than speed. Take these lessons very slowly.  Speed will come naturally later.  The <strong>accuracy level is set to 2%</strong>, so that does not leave you a very large error margin.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">As with the standard keypad, you must start in the HOME position.  Place the first three fingers of your right hand over the <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>4</key></span> <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>5</key></span> and <span class=\"keyhelp\"><key>6</key></span> keys of the keypad.  Your fingers should be poised just over the keys gently brushing them.  Use your pinkie to press ENTER and use the thumb of your left hand for spaces when necessary.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\"><span class=\"strong\">NOTE:  Make sure the <em>NUM LOCK</em> is on (a little light should shine on the keyboard.)</span></p>','Keypad',5,0,1,1),(337,3,'Гүнзгий шатыг дуусгах','Advanced Wrap Up','<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing mostly full paragraphs containing all kinds of letters, numbers, punctuation, etc.  If you don\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboard before starting the exercise.  Remember, hold down shift to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Just take your time and focus on accuracy.  You\\\'re already in the Advanced Course, so this should be a breeze for you.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">In this lesson you will be typing mostly full paragraphs containing all kinds of letters, numbers, punctuation, etc.  If you don\\\\\'t know a certain symbol, take a look at the on-screen keyboard before starting the exercise.  Remember, hold down shift to get the symbol on the top of a key.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Just take your time and focus on accuracy.  You\\\\\'re already in the Advanced Course, so this should be a breeze for you.</p>','Keyboard',6,0,1,0),(338,1,'Нүүр эгнээ ба гадна','Home row and Beyond','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Үгсийн санд тавтай морилно уу! Энэ хичээлээр Үндсэн Мөр дээрээс олдсон үгсээр эхлээд <strong><key>I</key> ба <key>E</key> товчлууруудыг</strong> аажмаар оруулсан бүх энгийн үгсүүдийг бичхэд зааж өгөх болно.</p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Та яарах хэрэггүй, эхлэх бүртээ өөрийнхөөрөө хий, Үндсэн Мөр дээр бүх үгс байгаа. Хаана товч байгааг хайх гэж гар-руугаа бүү хар, булчингийнхаа ой санамжийг ашиглах зуршилтай болохын тулд дэлгэцэн дээрх компьютерийн гараас лавлана уу!</p><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/homerow_ie.png\" alt=\"Keyboard Finger Position\" /></center>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Welcome to the world of words!  This lesson is going to teach you type very basic words starting with words found on the Home Row, and slowly introducing more letters, such as <strong>the <key>I</key> and <key>E</key> keys.</strong></p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Take your time and do your best to always start and end each words on the home row.  Never look at your hands to find where a key is, always refer to the onscreen keyboard to get into the habit of using your muscle memory to type!</p><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/homerow_ie.png\" alt=\"Keyboard Finger Position\" /></center>','Keyboard',4,0,1,1),(340,1,'Эрсдэлээс гарах','Venturing Out','<p class=\"typinghelp\">Энэ бол гар дээрх үлдсэн товчнуудыг гаргаж ирэх цаг болжээ. Энэ хичээл нь доод эгнээнд төвлөрөх тул ердийнхөөс арай удаан бичиж байгааг анзаарч магадгүй юм.</p><p><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/all_keys.png\" alt=\"Keyboard Finger Position\" /></center><br /></p><p class=\"typinghelp\">Гар руу бүү хар учир нь үргэлж таны хуруунууд үсэг бүрийн дараа Үндсэн Мөр дээр буцаж байрладаг.</p>','<p class=\"typinghelp\">It\\\\\'s time to venture out to the remaining keys on the keyboard.  This lesson will be very bottom-row-centric so you may notice yourself typing slower than normal.</p><p><center><img src=\"/tutor/images/intros/a